	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
		There are few choices -
<br>
<br>
a) It is simpler to implement our own protocol solution for the
<br>
registry, however, it may not be very scalable and extensible.
<br>
Therefore, I will explore how we can leverage some existing solution.
<br>
<br>
b) The p2pxwiki.com domain can be hosted on a machine which acts as
<br>
the "primary" authority for p2pxwiki virtual name registration. This
<br>
"primary" registry can later be replicated at any peer in a secure
<br>
manner (using certificates perhaps to ensure and verify the integrity
<br>
of the registry).  Actually, this replication architecture will be
<br>
very much like wiki replication. In wiki replication, peers need to
<br>
ensure that they are getting the correct copies of the wiki from
<br>
another peer whereas in the case of a registry, we need to ensure that
<br>
a domain name resolves to a correct ip address. The same principle
<br>
will avoid wiki hijacking as well as denial of service (because of
<br>
incorrect name resolution due to a malicious peers). I am sure similar
<br>
issues arise in traditional DNS, i will look into how it is solved and
<br>
if there is any implementation.
<br>
<br>
c) Once we replicate the registry to peers, the role of the central
<br>
registry will primarily be to ensure that the wiki names are unique
<br>
(i.e., cnn.p2pxwiki.com is not assigned to more than 1 master peer).
<br>
The mapping of name to IP address can in principle be resolved through
<br>
p2p discovery (some form of flooding) and need not go to central
<br>
registry.
<br>
<br>
I need to look at existing solutions on how they solve (b) in
<br>
particualr. I will explore today before proposing a spec for the
<br>
registry. I donot want to spend too much time looking at other
<br>
existing solutions, but at the same time, it is too easy to design our
<br>
own solution that may require significant effort later for scalability
<br>
and extensibility - so at the minimum i will need to come up with a
<br>
spec for the registry and identify what can be leveraged.
<br>
<br>
For an initial prototype demonstration, we donot need anything beyond
<br>
configuring the existing DNS Server at xwiki.com to divert
<br>
p2p.xwiki.com to a machine running the registry (after i have
<br>
developed it). Also p2pxwiki.com domain name needs to be registered
<br>
and needs to resolve to the machine which will run the registry. We do
<br>
not necessarily need a separate hosting at this point, we can use one
<br>
of the existing xwiki machines if it is ok.
<br>

	</td></tr>
