	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
		User Story 1    :: Offline XWiki 
<br>
<br>
John, a CNN news reporter, is on-board an airplane, and is scheduled to arrive 
<br>
in Atlanta at 3pm. He is returning after attending a conference on recent 
<br>
developments in media technology. CNN is scheduled to release a report on his 
<br>
experience at 4:10pm. He hears the announcement: "This is your captain speaking,
<br>
due to bad weather, the scheduled arrival time to Atlanta is now 4pm, please 
<br>
enjoy your coffee..." His heart skips a bit at the thought of missing the 
<br>
scheduled broadcast ! Suddenly he realizes that the AirBus is equipped 
<br>
with wireless connectivity, however because of bad weather, the connection will
<br>
be intermittent at best. 
<br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;The Offline XWiki comes to his rescue. He takes out his laptop, and starts 
<br>
working on the report that is due immediately upon arrival. He continues editing
<br>
the report and the updated changes are sent to his colleague Sara for review 
<br>
through the intermittent wireless connection. John and Sara work on the story 
<br>
together, with John doing most of the edits and Sara taking care of linking 
<br>
to other related reports and fixing typos. As the plane approaches Atlanta, 
<br>
the connection to the Internet improves, and he submits his final changes. 
<br>
Sara in CNN office is immediately notified of final changes, combines her edits 
<br>
with John's changes, and sends it immediately to John for final 
<br>
review. John, while waiting to get off the plane, notices that Sara has 
<br>
updated the report, reviews it before getting off and tells Sara that it looks 
<br>
good (as his watches the clock ticking 4:05pm !)  
<br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Sara immediately hand off a copy of the news to the producer and the news is 
<br>
broadcast as scheduled at 4:10 ! XWiki saves the day one more time, and both 
<br>
John  and Sara are commended on the great story.  
<br>
