	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
		User Story 2  :: Sharing of multiple pages
<br>
<br>
Not long ago, in a place not far away ...
<br>
<br>
There was a company, called "noname", in the business of bringing
<br>
uptodate news to the people. The organization structure of the company
<br>
was complex - with different people in charge of bringing different
<br>
stories. Heather was in charge of weather, S. Ports was in charge of
<br>
sports. For Business there was Minesh, and for Politics there was
<br>
Kudovics. Each person works on different stories and has to travel
<br>
frequently, many times to locations with weak or no
<br>
infrastructure. Moreover, everyone has to confer with the others and
<br>
relate to other reports to make a compelling story. For this, they
<br>
used to fly to the headquarter and have a conference meeting before
<br>
each news broadcast, costing "noname" lots of money in travel
<br>
expenses. Moreover, once the meeting is over and there was no easy way
<br>
to incorporate further changes made by other.
<br>
&nbsp;
<br>
Then came P2PXWiki - it saved name for "noname" and changed the way
<br>
communication happened. Heather, S. Ports, Minesh, and Kudovics formed
<br>
a peer-group and could communicate with each other as peers at
<br>
different physical locations even with weak connectivities. All of
<br>
them worked on different stories frequently exchanging comments. For
<br>
instance, Heather predicts rainy weather in Atlanta for the next two
<br>
days, and consequently, S. Ports announces bad day for the local
<br>
sports.  As soon as changes are made in one news story, it is
<br>
propagated to other members of the group. Everyone can comment on each
<br>
others story, and refer to it easily while reporting their section of
<br>
the news. Real-time communications within the peer-group ensured that
<br>
each story was most up-to-date, comprehensive, and is published as it
<br>
happened.
<br>
<br>
P2PXwiki saved "noname" a lot of money in financial expenses, and beat
<br>
the rival "some-name" in popularity! Soon Heather, S. Ports, Minesh
<br>
and Kudovics became famous and their team called the "WikiNews"!
<br>
<br>
PS: All characters in this story are fictional.. any resemblence to
<br>
anyone is purely intentional :) 
<br>
<br>
PPS: I am just trying something for fun, other stories won't probably be
<br>
like this one... Please send  me a message if you think I am going overboard.
