	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
		User Story 3 :: Multiple wikis being shared Example of content sharing
<br>
<br>John is on a road-trip with his family after a busy week at work.
Being a very busy professional, he had limited time to plan his trip in
detail. John knew that their road-trip to the Aquarium goes through
many interesting places - although he didn't have all the details.
However, he also knew that XWiki will help him out. <br>
<br>
While John drives, his wife Martha takes out the laptop and starts
searching for information on interesting places nearby by connecting to
other peer travelers. XWiki automatically detects other nearby
travelers and connects them as peers while each of them possibly
travels at 70 miles per hour on the interstate. Martha find out by
looking at the wiki of a nearby peer that there is a mini-golf course
nearby. Looking for something more exciting, she starts searching for
information on "scenic places" through the peer-network. Through the
P2PXwiki network, she finds information and route to the fabulous
"smokey mountains" nearby. She even looks at interesting pictures taken
by others on their prior trip to "smokey mountain". She shows them to
John and they both decide to stop by the "smokeys" to enjoy the
breathtaking views. <br>
<br>
Meanwhile, their 12 year old son who likes solving puzzles, is playing
with his IPAQ. His IPAQ is equiped with XWiki. He starts connecting his
XWiki with other peers, and searches for "ongoing puzzles". Sure
enough, he finds other fellow travelers playing different games. The
name "Lateral Puzzles" caught his attention and he joins the game. The
game works as follows: the host posts a situation, and the other
players try to find a logical explanation of the puzzle by asking
questions. The host provides only "yes/no" answers to the questions,
and other players use it as clues to solve the puzzle. Junior John also
joins the game and starts following up questions by other peers and
asks his questions to solve the puzzle. There is a murder mystery to
solve - "A man is lying dead in a field. Next to him there is an
unopened package. There is no other creature in the field. How did he
die?". Some fellow passenger had asked - "did he die from hunger"?The
host replied "no", another question followed "Did he die of
sunstroke?", "no" came the answer in wiki comment from the host.. John
Jr. joins the game and starts asking question of his own... <br>
<br>
As they approached the smokey mountains, John and Martha get ready to
take exciting pictures and enjoy the view, and by the time they get off
the car, their son has solved a murder mystery and tells his parents
how happy he is. It turned out that - The man had jumped from a plane
but his parachute had failed to open. It is the unopened package that
is lying in the field. <br>
<br>
John and Martha are very happy at their experience, having used XWiki
to locate smokey mountains, and helping their son do useful mental
exercise through the game ! They share their experience with other
travelers on their way back. <br>
<br>

