	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
		User Story 4 :: More delay between updates and possibly conflicting updates
<br>
<br>
<br>
Xwiki is widely used in the classrooms for interaction between students
and teacher. Mike, a student in "Introduction to CS" class frequently
takes notes during the class and shares it on the wiki. Other fellow
students also share their notes taken during the class on the class
wiki. The Class Wiki allows sharing of notes among students and also
helps the instructor in understanding any concerns of the class
allowing better communication during subsequent lectures. Simultaneous
updates by students often give rise to conflicts on the same page,
however xwiki automatically resolves most of the conflicts since
contents are mostly additions to a page. On some rare occasions, it
takes input from the person doing the updates in resolving conflicts. <br>
<br>
Students often look at notes at home and away from the classroom.
P2PXWiki allows students to access the classroom notes when offline -
which is sometimes the case when they are at home because of parental
control. When connected with other students, XWiki automatically takes
care of sending the updated contents to other students and the
instructor facilitating class discussions. <br>

	</td></tr>
