	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
		User Story 5 :: Security (I share my wiki with a friend)
<br>
<br>
John, our frequent traveler, has very different security requirements
<br>
from our WikiNews team ! While traveling on vacation, John likes to share
<br>
his content with other fellow travelers freely. He selects 
<br>
communication channel within p2pxwiki that allows anyone to login and
<br>
share contents with any other available peers. John can even select
<br>
anonymous connections whereby only limited information from his profile
<br>
will be shared with the peers without revealing his complete identity. 
<br>
<br>
The WikiNews team, on the other hand, work in a group and with much
<br>
stricter security requirements. Competition from rival news companies
<br>
means that all communication within the group should be secure and
<br>
authenticated. The communication data should travel through secure
<br>
channels and only allowed from authorized members of the group. P2PXwiki
<br>
facilitates this by a simple user option to select completely secure
<br>
channels while establishing  communication within the peer group. All the
<br>
details concerning authentication, authorization, confidentiality, and 
<br>
data integrity is handled by the underlying communication layer.  
<br>

