	<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
Using p2psockets at present is going to be significant debugging
exercise with perhaps lots of surprises ! The reason is that the
website <a href="http://p2psockets.jxta.org/">http://p2psockets.jxta.org/</a>
says the project has completed its research goals on 6/15/05. I checked
the mailing lists and don't see much communication - the developer
mailing list has 30 emails in 14 months with some of them spams. <br>
also the release file i downloaded doesn't have source code for xml-rpc
port or any examples on how to use it. I looked at the jar, and instead
of apache's org.apache.xmlrpc.WebServer class, the port has
org.apache.xmlrpc.P2PWebServer; which means the code written with
apache's xml-rpc won't work as it is without changes as claimed ! I may
be wrong about this, but there is no examples/docs in the release to
show correct usage. <br>
<br>
So, I think p2psockets is premature at this stage to be used by us,
using it requires significant hack. I will instead just use another
xml-rpc port on jxta (<a href="http://xmlrpc.jxta.org/">http://xmlrpc.jxta.org/</a>) to build the registry which i need to develop anyway. 
